<section>
  <div
    class="mx-auto w-full lg:px-24 max-w-7xl md:px-12 items-center px-8 py-24 scroll-mt-12"
  >
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 lg:gap-12">
      <div class="text-center lg:text-left">
        <div>
          <p
            class="text-3xl font-normal tracking-tight text-black font-display"
          >
            Frequently asked questions
          </p>
          <p class="text-base mt-4 text-zinc-500">
            Answers to commonly asked questions and concerns about BeautyMark.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

<div
        x-data="{
  activeAccordion: '',
  setActiveAccordion(id) {
  this.activeAccordion = (this.activeAccordion == id) ? '' : id
  }
  }"
        class="relative w-full mx-auto font-normal lg:col-span-2"
      >
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-black"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span>My Pro status keeps getting reset after a day</span>
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-pink-500 -rotate-[45deg]"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div x-show="activeAccordion==id" x-collapse="">
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              This is an unfortunate quirk of how TestFlight works, and will be gone when we're out of Beta. In TestFlight, 
time passes at an accelerated scale (each day only lasts 4 irl minutes 😅), and subscriptions get paused after 12 auto-renewals. Since
you're not actually charged for any purchases while still in Beta, we recommend "purchasing" the "Lifetime" option, which doesn't 
expire. We'll reset that for you when we launch the app in the AppStore, and we're no longer at the mercy of TestFlight's quirks.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      <div
        x-data="{
  activeAccordion: '',
  setActiveAccordion(id) {
  this.activeAccordion = (this.activeAccordion == id) ? '' : id
  }
  }"
        class="relative w-full mx-auto font-normal lg:col-span-2"
      >
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-black"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span>What is a collection?</span>
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-pink-500 -rotate-[45deg]"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div x-show="activeAccordion==id" x-collapse="">
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              A collection is a grouped folders of related products. For example, 
              we have “Travel” (for small sized things you should remember to pack), 
              “Wishlist” (for products we don’t have but would like to buy when they go on sale) or 
              “Favourite sunscreens” (for when friends ask Brittany what her favourite Korean sunscreen is 😅)
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span
              >The brand I'm looking for won't autocomplete.</span
            >
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-pink-500"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              That’s ok! Although we’ve added around 900 brands from Sephora, 
              Ulta and Yesstyle, we haven’t caught them all. The textfields 
              are also free-input, so you can just type in the brand that you have.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span
              >The app crashed when I was cropping my screenshot</span
            >
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-pink-500"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              Woof. This is a bug we’re aware of but haven’t made headway towards fixing it. We think the problem happens when you press down (i.e. a loooooong tap gesture) while cropping. We know it’s annoying and we’re very sorry about this! 
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span
              >Can I use the app without subscribing?</span
            >
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-pink-500"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              Absolutely! While you won’t have access to all the features available, you can create up to 20 products and 1 collection. 
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span
              >I can’t upgrade to Pro</span
            >
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-pink-500"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              Oh no! Make sure that you have a good internet connection, and that you’re signed in with your Apple ID. If it still doesn’t work, send us an email at support@beautymark.app and we’ll help you get it sorted out.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span>My products aren’t syncing across devices</span>
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-pink-500"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              This usually means that there’s something wrong with your iCloud setup. Make sure 
              that the information displayed in Settings &rarr; Data Management under the 
              iCloud Status section makes sense. A green icon with a “Synced to iCloud message” 
              means everything is a-ok. A red “error” icon means something is wrong. Make sure 
              that you’ve enabled “Background App Refresh” (in iOS Settings &rarr; Apps &rarr; BeautyMark). 
              Try killing and restarting the app, and giving it a couple of seconds to make another 
              attempt at connecting to your iCloud. If you’re still having problems, send 
              us an email at support@beautymark.app
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span
              >What’s a local backup?</span
            >
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-pink-500"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              Under Settings &rarr; Data Management, you’ll see a Local Backups section. 
              While the app is still in Beta, we’re aware that some changes might 
              break your products, no matter how hard we try to avoid it. In these cases, 
              if you have made a local backup, you can try to restore it and hope 
              all your products get re-imported correctly
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-pink-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span>My local backups aren’t syncing across devices</span>
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-pink-500"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              This is expected. Your local backups are local to your 
              device, so that you can restore your products even when 
              something goes wrong with the products saved in your iCloud.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
